ce:section.ce:para:
To explore the tunable optical properties, the three different phenylenediamine isomers in ethanol solution are used to initially synthesized the CQDs. The obtained three CQDs are marked as oCDs, mCDs and pCDs (Fig. 1
                        ), respectively. The morphology and size are evaluated using TEM. As shown in Fig. 2
                        , it can be seen that the three samples are demonstrating monodispersed nanoparticles with a rather homogeneous size distribution. Notably, the oCDs, mCDs pCDs are nearly spherical (the corresponding size distribution conforms to the Gaussian distribution according to the statistically analyzed results from 50 nanoparticles and the histogram in Fig. 2) with an average diameters of about 1.6, 1.5 and 3 nm, respectively, indicating that the the start carbon sources can affect the size of CQDs.
